|first=John|last=Weckert|first2=Stuart|last2=Ferguson|title=Ethics, reference and expert systems|journal=Australian Library Journal|volume=42|year=1993}}\n* {{cite journal|first=Mark|last=Johnston|first2=John|last2=Weckert|title=Machine learning for library monograph selection|journal=Expert Systems for Information Management|volume=4|year=1991}}\n* {{cite journal|first=John|last=Weckert|title=Functionalism's impotence|journal=Philosophical Inquiry|volume=12|year=1990}}\n* {{cite journal|first=John|last=Weckert|first2=Clare|last2=Cooper|title=Artificial intelligence, expert systems and librarianship: a review of the literature|journal=Australian Library Review|volume=7|year=1990}}\n* {{cite journal|first=Mark|last=Johnston|first2=John|last2=Weckert|title=Selection advise: an expert system for collection development|journal=Information Technology and Libraries|volume=9|year=1990}}\n* {{cite journal|last=John|first=Weckert|first2=Clare|last2=Cooper|title=Expert systems and libraries|journal=Riverina Library Review|volume=6|year=1989}}\n* {{cite journal|first=John|last=Weckert|title=The theory-ladenness of observations|journal=Studies in History and Philosophy of Science|volume=17|year=1986}}\n* {{cite journal|first=John|last=Weckert|title=Putnam, reference and essentialism|journal=Dialogue|volume=25|year=1986}}\n* {{cite journal|first=John|last=Weckert|title=Is relativism self-refuting?|journal=Educational Philosophy and Theory|volume=16|year=1984}}\n\n===Books===\n* {{cite book|first=James|last=Moor|first2=John|last2=Weckert|title=Nanoethics: The Ethical and Social Implications of Nanotechnology|publisher=MIT Press|year=2007}}\n* {{cite book|editor1-first=Jeroen|editor1-last=van den Hoven|editor2-first=John|editor2-last=Weckert|title=Information Technology and Moral Philosophy|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=2007}}\n* {{cite book|editor-first=John|editor-last=Weckert|title=Computer Ethics|publisher=Ashgate|year=2007}}\n* {{cite book|editor1-first=Fritz|editor1-last=Allhoff|editor2-first=Patrick|editor2-last=Lin|editor3-first=James|editor3-last=Moor |editor4-first=John|editor4-last=Weckert| display-editors = 3|title=Nanotechnology: A Maelstrom of Ethical and Social Issues|publisher=Wiley|year=2007}}\n* {{cite book|editor1-first=Emma|editor1-last=Rooksby|editor2-first=John|editor2-last=Weckert|title=Information Technology and Social Justice|publisher=Idea Group|year=2007}}\n* {{cite book|editor-first=John|editor-last=Weckert|title=Electronic Monitoring in the Workplace: Controversies and Solutions|publisher=Idea Group|year=2004}}\n* Weckert, John; Al-Saggaf, Yeslam (eds), ''Selected papers from the Computers and Philosophy (CAP) conference, The Australian National University, 13 October \u2013 2 November 2003.'' CRPIT, vol 37: Australian Computer Society, Sydney.\n* {{cite book\n| editor1-first = John\n| editor1-last  = Weckert\n| editor2-first = Craig\n| editor2-last  = McDonald\n| title         = Intelligent Library Systems: Proceedings of the Intelligent Library Systems conference, Charles Sturt University, September, 1992\n| publisher     = Centre for Information Studies (CSU)\n| year          = 1992}}\n* {{cite book|editor1-first=Craig|editor1-last=McDonald|editor2-first=John|editor2-last=Weckert|title=Libraries and Expert Systems, |publisher=Taylor Graham|location=London|year=1991}} (Proceedings of the Libraries and Expert Systems conference, Charles Sturt University \u2013 Riverina, July 1990).\n\n==See also==\n* [[Trust (social sciences)|Trust]]: Trust in an online environment\n* [[Cheating]]: Cheating in an online environment\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Weckert, John}}\n[[Category:Australian philosophers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Charles Sturt University faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Melbourne alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Adelaide alumni]]\n[[Category:La Trobe University alumni]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "name_user": "Chris the speller", "label": "safe", "comment": "cap", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Weckert"}
{"title_page": "Guillaume Lemans", "text_new": "'''Guillaume Lemans''' is a [[France|French]] screenwriter and film producer.<ref>[http://popwire.com.sg/guillaume-lemans/ \"Screenwriter Guillaume Lemans on zombie movies, sci-fi in French cinema, and adapting comic-books\"]. ''PopWire''.</ref> He received a [[Canadian Screen Award]] nomination for [[Canadian Screen Award for Best Screenplay|Best Original Screenplay]] at the [[7th Canadian Screen Awards]] in 2019 for ''[[Just a Breath Away]] (Dans la brume)''.<ref>[https://info-culture.biz/2019/02/07/prix-ecrans-canadiens-2019-finalistes-2019-canadian-screen-awards-nominees-announced/ \"Prix \u00c9crans canadiens 2019 les finalistes sont\u2026 / 2019 Canadian Screen Awards nominees announced\"]. ''InfoCulture'', February 7, 2019.</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n*''[[Anything for Her]] (Pour elle)'' - 2008\n*''[[Beauties at War]] (La guerre des Miss)'' - 2008\n*''[[Caged (2010 film)|Caged]] (Captifs)'' - 2010\n*''[[Point Blank (2010 film)|Point Blank]] (\u00c0 bout portant)'' - 2010\n*''Final Balance (L\u00e9gitime D\u00e9fense)'' - 2011\n*''Le Marquis'' (2011)\n*''[[Mea Culpa (film)|Mea Culpa]]'' - 2014\n*''[[A Perfect Man (2015 film)|A Perfect Man]] (Un homme id\u00e9al)'' - 2015<ref>[https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/a-perfect-man-homme-ideal-783269 \"'A Perfect Man' ('Un Homme Ideal'): Film Review\"]. ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', March 24, 2015.</ref>\n*''Burn Out'' - 2017\n*''[[Just a Breath Away]] (Dans la brume)'' - 2018\n*''[[The Night Eats the World]] (La nuit a d\u00e9vor\u00e9 le monde)'' - 2019\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb name|3280198}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lemans, Guillaume}}\n[[Category:21st-century French male writers]]\n[[Category:French male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:French film producers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{France-film-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Guillaume Lemans''' is