{"title_page": "Parti Bumi Kenyalang", "text_new": "{{Infobox political party\n| country         = Malaysia\n| name            = Land of the Hornbill Party\n| native_name     = Parti Bumi Kenyalang<br />\u80af\u96c5\u5170\u5168\u6c11\u515a\n| logo            = File:Parti Bumi Kenyalang.jpg\n| logo_size       = \n| abbreviation    = PBK\n| leader          = Voon Lee Shan\n| foundation      = \n| legalised       = 2013\n| dissolution     =\n| headquarters    = [[Bintulu]], [[Sarawak]], Malaysia\n| youth_wing      = \n| membership_year =\n| membership      =\n| ideology        = [[Regionalism (politics)|Sarawak regionalism]]<br />[[Self-determination|Self determination]]\n| position        = [[Centrist|Centre]]\n| national        =\n| international   =\n| colours         = {{Color box|#FBC625|border=darkgray}} Gold, Red, Black\n| colorcode       = gold\n| seats1_title    = [[Dewan Negara]]:\n| seats1          = {{Composition bar|0|70|hex=maroon}}\n| seats2_title    = [[Dewan Rakyat]]:\n| seats2          = {{Composition bar|0|222|hex=maroon}}\n| seats3_title    = [[Dewan Undangan Negeri]]:\n| seats3          = {{Composition bar|0|587|hex=maroon}}\n| flag            =\n| website         = [[https://www.facebook.com/InQuestOfIndependence/?ref=page_internal Party Bumi Kenyalang Official Facebook]]\n| footnotes       =\n}}\n\nThe '''''Parti Bumi Kenyalang''''' ('''PBK''', Land of the Hornbill Party) is a  [[political party]] registered in 2013 and based in [[Bintulu]], [[Sarawak]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fz.com/content/ros-approves-20-new-political-parties|title=ROS approves 20 new political parties|date=2 September 2013|author=Bernama|work=fz.com|accessdate=9 April 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20160409200245/http://www.fz.com/content/ros-approves-20-new-political-parties|archivedate=9 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe party's stated intent is to establish a just, equal, progressive, stable and harmonious society and serve as a platform for Sarawakians to express their concerns about issues affecting the state and safeguard the concerns and autonomy of the state <ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2013-10-26 |title=Parti Bumi Kenyalang explained by pro tem secretary |work=The Star |location=Malaysia }}</ref>. It also seeks to push for a review of the status of the rights of the state of Sarawak using the [[Malaysia Agreement]] and the [[Cobbold Commission]] report as its basis <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ehornbill.com/v12/2012-11-06-12-08-00/2012-11-06-12-18-00/6469-parti-bumi-kenyalang |title=Menyeru memperluaskan Jawatankuasa untuk menuntut kembali hak autoriti kepada Sabah dan Sarawak dan membuat Agenda laporan Kerja |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=2016-06-04 |website=eHornbill |publisher= |access-date=2018-06-06 |quote=}}</ref>. Parti Bumi Kenyalang is the only political party currently working on the concept of \"In Quest of Independence\"  which is gaining support from Sarawak people. When Sarawak people give Parti Bumi Kenyalang full support and become Sarawak government, Parti Bumi Kenyalang will unilaterally declare independence (UDI) in DUN from federation of Malaysia based on United Nations Article 1541 and 1514.\n\n==2019 leadership <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theborneopost.com/2019/06/10/voon-lee-shan-is-pbk-president/}}</ref>==   \n* '''President'''\n** Voon Lee Shan \n\n* '''Deputy President'''\n** Peli Aron\n\n* '''Vice President'''\n** Awang Badele\n** Peter Asut\n** Dato George Martin\n\n* '''Secretary-general'''\n** Priscilla Lau\n\n* '''Assistant Secretary'''\n** Annie Lau Siew Ching\n\n* '''Treasurer-general'''\n** Jamie Tiew Yen Houng\n* '''Assistant Treasurer'''\n** Ralikrishnan Wong\n\n* '''Organizing Secretary'''\n** Pelly Lee Oui Lea\n\n* '''Assistant Organizing Secretary'''\n** Devora Chung Siew Yen\n\n* '''Publicity and Information Chief'''\n**  Arthur Wong Yuk Chu\n\n==2018 general election==\n\nThe party made its electoral debut in the [[Malaysian general election, 2018|2018 general election]] by contesting the [[Sarikei (federal constituency)|Sarikei parliamentary seat]] but only managed to garner 392 votes resulting in the loss of the candidate's deposit.\n\n==2018 Leadership==\n\n* '''President'''\n** Yu Chang Ping \n\n* '''Vice-President'''\n** Ngelayan Unan\n\n* '''Secretary-General'''\n** Rali Wong Yew Lik\n\n* '''Deputy Secretary'''\n** Yu Chin Liik\n\n* '''Assistant Secretaries'''\n** Ling K K\n** Jessie Ngelayang\n\n* '''Treasurer'''\n** Ling Mee Hua\n\n* '''Assistant Treasurer'''\n** Lai Chii Chuan\n\n* '''Organising Secretary'''\n** Lau Ing Siong\n\n==External links==\n\n* [https://www.facebook.com/pbksarawakian/ Parti Bumi Kenyalang] on [[Facebook]]\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Malaysian political parties}}\n\n[[Category:Political parties established in 2013]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:2013 establishments in Malaysia]]\n\n\n{{Malaysia-party-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox political party\n| country         = Malaysia\n| name            = Land of the Hornbill Party\n| native_name     = \n| lang1 = Bahasa Sarawak/ Malay\n| name_lang1 = Parti Bumi Kenyalang\n| lang2 = Chinese\n| name_lang2 = \u80af\u96c5\u5170\u5168\u6c11\u515a<br>''K\u011bny\u01cel\u00e1n Qu\u00e1nm\u00ednd\u01ceng''\n| logo            = File:Parti Bumi Kenyalang.jpg\n| logo_size       = \n| abbreviation    = PBK\n| foundation      = \n| legalised       = 2013\n| dissolution     =\n| headquarters    = [[Bintulu]], [[Sarawak]]\n| youth_wing      = \n| membership_year =\n| membership      =\n| ideology        = [[Regionalism (politics)|Sarawak regionalism]]<br />[[Self-determination|Self determination]]\n| position        = [[Centrist|Centre]]\n| national        =\n| international   =\n| president = [[Voon Lee Shan]]\n| leader1_title = Deputy President\n| leader1_name = [[Peli Aron]]\n| leader2_title = Vice President\n| leader2_name = [[Awang Badele]], [[Peter Asut]], [[Dato George Martin]]\n| colours         = {{Color box|#FBC625|border=darkgray}} Gold, {{Color box|#FF0000|border=darkgray}} Red, {{Color box|#000000|border=darkgray}} Black\n| colorcode       = gold\n| seats1_title    = [[Dewan Negara]]:\n| seats1          = {{Composition bar|0|70|hex=maroon}}\n| seats2_title    = [[Dewan Rakyat]]:\n| seats2          = {{Composition bar|0|222|hex=maroon}}\n| seats3_title    = [[Sarawak State Legislative Assembly|Dewan Undangan Negeri]]:\n| seats3          = {{Composition bar|0|82|hex=maroon}}\n| flag            =\n| website         = [[http://e-pbk.com/|Party Bumi Kenyalang Website]]\n| footnotes       = [[https://www.facebook.com/InQuestOfIndependence|Party Bumi Kenyalang Official Facebook]]\n}}\n\nThe '''''Parti Bumi Kenyalang''''' ('''PBK''', Land of the Hornbill Party) is a Sarawakian [[political party]] registered in 2013 and based in [[Bintulu]], [[Sarawak]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fz.com/content/ros-approves-20-new-political-parties|title=ROS approves 20 new political parties|date=2 September 2013|author=Bernama|work=fz.com|accessdate=9 April 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20160409200245/http://www.fz.com/content/ros-approves-20-new-political-parties|archivedate=9 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe party's stated intent is to establish a just, equal, progressive, stable and harmonious society and serve as a platform for Sarawakians to express their concerns about issues affecting the state and safeguard the concerns and autonomy of Sarawak<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2013-10-26 |title=Parti Bumi Kenyalang explained by pro tem secretary |work=The Star |location=Malaysia }}</ref>.\n\nIt also seeks to push for a review of the status of the rights of Sarawak using the [[Malaysia Agreement]] and the [[Cobbold Commission]] report as its basis <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ehornbill.com/v12/2012-11-06-12-08-00/2012-11-06-12-18-00/6469-parti-bumi-kenyalang |title=Menyeru memperluaskan Jawatankuasa untuk menuntut kembali hak autoriti kepada Sabah dan Sarawak dan membuat Agenda laporan Kerja |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=2016-06-04 |website=eHornbill |publisher= |access-date=2018-06-06 |quote=}}</ref>. Parti Bumi Kenyalang is the only political party currently working on the concept of \"In Quest of Independence\"  which is gaining support from Sarawak people. \n\nAs a pro-independence political party, Parti Bumi Kenyalang will seek freedom and independence for Sarawak by constitutional and legal means under domestic and international law based on inalienable right of self-determination mentioned in United Nations Assembly Resolutions 1514 and 1541 from the federation of Malaysia once it becomes the Sarawak Government.\n\n==2019 leadership <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theborneopost.com/2019/06/10/voon-lee-shan-is-pbk-president/}}</ref>==   \n* '''President'''\n** [[Voon Lee Shan]]\n\n* '''Deputy President'''\n** Peli Aron\n\n* '''Vice President'''\n** Awang Badele\n** Peter Asut\n** Dato George Martin\n\n* '''Secretary-general'''\n** Priscilla Lau\n\n* '''Assistant Secretary'''\n** Annie Lau Siew Ching\n\n* '''Treasurer-general'''\n** Jamie Tiew Yen Houng\n* '''Assistant Treasurer'''\n** Ralikrishnan Wong\n\n* '''Organizing Secretary'''\n** Pelly Lee Oui Lea\n\n* '''Assistant Organizing Secretary'''\n** Devora Chung Siew Yen\n\n* '''Publicity and Information Chief'''\n**  Arthur Wong Yuk Chu\n\n==2018 general election==\n\nThe party made its electoral debut in the [[Malaysian general election, 2018|2018 general election]] by contesting the [[Sarikei (federal constituency)|Sarikei parliamentary seat]] but only managed to garner 392 votes resulting in the loss of the candidate's deposit.\n\n==2018 Leadership==\n\n* '''President'''\n** Yu Chang Ping \n\n* '''Vice-President'''\n** Ngelayan Unan\n\n* '''Secretary-General'''\n** Rali Wong Yew Lik\n\n* '''Deputy Secretary'''\n** Yu Chin Liik\n\n* '''Assistant Secretaries'''\n** Ling K K\n** Jessie Ngelayang\n\n* '''Treasurer'''\n** Ling Mee Hua\n\n* '''Assistant Treasurer'''\n** Lai Chii Chuan\n\n* '''Organising Secretary'''\n** Lau Ing Siong\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.facebook.com/InQuestOfIndependence|Parti Bumi Kenyalang] on [[Facebook]]\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Malaysian political parties}}\n\n[[Category:Political parties established in 2013]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:2013 establishments in Malaysia]]\n\n\n{{Malaysia-party-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Vif12vf", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Reverted to revision 949593756 byVif12vf(talk): Several of these changes are purely disruptive. For instance, dont change the country!  (TW))", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parti_Bumi_Kenyalang"}
